[TRACE] /home/pc/projects/opensassi/a0/src/deepseek_provider.cpp:152 tool-call request body: {"max_tokens":4096,"messages":[{"content":"You are a system agent that operates in a Linux 6.17.0-35-generic x86_64 environment using the command line via system_bash to execute commands on behalf of a user.\n\nWhen given instructions, execute each step immediately by calling the appropriate tool. Do not ask for confirmation, do not describe what you will do — just do it. Call tools directly by their short names. After completing all steps, present the result.\n\n## Always-available tools (call by short name)\nbash, read, glob, grep, edit, write, show_skills, show_skill_tools, tools_for_prompt\n","role":"system"},{"content":"read technical-specification.md","role":"user"},{"content":"```json\n{\n  \"intent\": \"Read the contents of a file named 'technical-specification.md'\",\n  \"plan\": \"Use the 'read' tool from /system/fs to read the file. First, try to find the file using 'glob' or 'grep' to determine its location, then read its contents.\",\n  \"tools\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"glob\",\n      \"schema\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"pattern\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Glob pattern to find 'technical-specification.md' (e.g. **/technical-specification.md)\"\n          },\n          \"path\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Root directory to search in (e.g., current working directory)\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\"pattern\"]\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"read\",\n      \"schema\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"file_path\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Absolute path to the file 'technical-specification.md' to read\"\n          },\n          \"limit\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"description\": \"Optional maximum number of lines to read (default 2000)\"\n          },\n          \"offset\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"description\": \"Optional starting line number (1-indexed, default 1)\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\"file_path\"]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```","role":"assistant"},{"content":"","role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"function":{"arguments":"{\"pattern\":\"**/technical-specification.md\"}","name":"glob"},"id":"call_00_U4VAGp0MYKv2900xQVBT2859","type":"function"}]},{"content":"./technical-specification.md\n./src/skills/technical-specification.md\n./src/persistence/technical-specification.md\n./src/docker/technical-specification.md\n./src/c2/technical-specification.md\n./src/b1/technical-specification.md","role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_00_U4VAGp0MYKv2900xQVBT2859"},{"content":"","role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"function":{"arguments":"{\"command\":\"pwd\",\"description\":\"Print current working directory\"}","name":"bash"},"id":"call_00_ywNP5bIbc3G4MgpuAQ7O6511","type":"function"}]},{"content":"/home/pc/projects/opensassi/a0/.a0/worktrees/a0-session-7aaf7148\n","role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_00_ywNP5bIbc3G4MgpuAQ7O6511"},{"content":"","role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"function":{"arguments":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/pc/projects/opensassi/a0/.a0/worktrees/a0-session-7aaf7148/technical-specification.md\"}","name":"read"},"id":"call_00_lcvzSoNMsbvQLMRp3W9e1366","type":"function"}]},{"content":"1: # Technical Paper: Minimal Component‑Based Agent (C++ Implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Version 2.1 – Docker Integration and Containerized Execution\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## 1. Overview\n8: \n9: This document provides the complete technical specification and development plan for a **minimal self‑evolving agent** written in **C++17**. The agent connects to the DeepSeek API, maintains a file‑based repository of **tools** (atomic bash commands) and **skills** (LLM prompts with eager tool calls, parameter substitution, optional validators), and runs inside a VM isolation environment (or directly on a host). All logs are stored locally.\n10: \n11: **Core features**:\n12: \n13: - Tools and skills share JSON Schema I/O (strings, arrays, objects).\n14: - Skills support **eager tool calls** (`{{tool:name ...}}`) that execute before the LLM request.\n15: - Skills support **parameter substitution** (`{{key}}`) where `key` is a field from the invocation parameters (e.g., `{{goal}}`).\n16: - **Validators** (optional chain of tools) process the LLM response; validators are simple tool names (future extension for transformation bindings).\n17: - **Dependencies** declared per skill (tools and other skills required) – **must be checked before execution**.\n18: - **Timeout enforcement** for all tool executions (30 seconds default).\n19: - **Docker execution mode**: Tools can run inside isolated containers (default Ubuntu 22.04) with configurable trust levels (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW), shared container pools, custom images, and `apt` dependencies. Skills can bring up multi‑service environments using `docker-compose.yml`.\n20: - Performance monitoring (optional, for future C++ optimization).\n21: - Session replay via local JSON Lines logs.\n22: \n23: This specification includes **architectural and procedural guardrails** that would have prevented common implementation omissions, such as missing dependency checks, ignored parameter substitution, absent subprocess timeouts, and incomplete `args` mode handling. The Docker sub‑module is a **required** extension for containerized execution.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## 2. Component Specifications (C++ Interfaces)\n28: \n29: The following interfaces are defined in `agent_interfaces.h`. They use modern C++17/20 features (`std::variant`, `std::optional`, smart pointers). No inheritance except abstract base classes.\n30: \n31: **Key types**:\n32: \n33: ```cpp\n34: using StructuredValue = std::variant<nullptr_t, bool, double, std::string,\n35:                                      std::vector<StructuredValue>,\n36:                                      std::unordered_map<std::string, StructuredValue>>;\n37: using JSONSchema = std::unordered_map<std::string, StructuredValue>;\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### 2.1 Core Data Structures\n41: \n42: ```cpp\n43: enum class TrustLevel {\n44:     HIGH,      // shared container across all high-trust tools\n45:     MEDIUM,    // shared container across all medium-trust tools\n46:     LOW        // one container per (image, tool name) combination\n47: };\n48: \n49: struct Tool {\n50:     std::string name;\n51:     std::string description;\n52:     std::string command;\n53:     // \"stdin\": params JSON is serialized and piped to the command's stdin.\n54:     // \"args\":  params is a JSON object; each top-level key-value pair is passed as a command-line argument\n55:     //          in the form --key=value (if value is string/number) or just value (if key is \"_\").\n56:     //          For a non-object params, the whole value is passed as a single argument.\n57:     //          Arguments are shell-escaped.\n58:     std::string inputMode = \"stdin\";\n59: \n60:     // Docker execution (optional – if dockerImage empty, run on host)\n61:     std::string dockerImage;                     // e.g., \"ubuntu:22.04\"\n62:     TrustLevel trustLevel = TrustLevel::MEDIUM;\n63:     bool useContainerPool = true;                // false = ephemeral docker run --rm\n64:     std::vector<std::string> aptDependencies;    // packages to install via apt\n65:     int timeoutSecs = 30;                        // per-tool timeout override\n66: };\n67: \n68: struct ToolCall {\n69:     std::string id;\n70:     std::string name;\n71:     json arguments;\n72: };\n73: \n74: struct ToolSchema {\n75:     std::string name;\n76:     std::string description;\n77:     json inputSchema;\n78: };\n79: \n80: struct ValidatorBinding {\n81:     std::string toolName;\n82:     std::optional<std::string> transform; // future: JSONPath binding\n83: };\n84: \n85: struct Prompt {\n86:     std::string name;\n87:     std::string description;\n88:     std::string prompt;                   // may contain {{tool:...}} and {{key}} placeholders\n89:     std::vector<std::string> dependencies;    // tool and prompt names required\n90:     std::vector<ValidatorBinding> validators; // post-LLM processing chain\n91:     std::string ns;                            // namespace context for qualified-name resolution\n92:     std::string component;                     // component context for qualified-name resolution\n93: \n94:     // Docker compose support\n95:     std::string composeFile;                     // path to docker-compose.yml (relative to skill dir)\n96:     std::vector<std::string> aptDependencies;    // rolled up into container(s) used by prompt's tools\n97: };\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### 2.2 Abstract Interfaces\n101: \n102: ```cpp\n103: class SkillRegistry {\n104: public:\n105:     virtual ~SkillRegistry() = default;\n106:     virtual bool loadFromDirectory(const std::string& path) = 0;\n107:     virtual std::optional<Tool> getTool(const std::string& name) const = 0;\n108:     virtual std::optional<Skill> getSkill(const std::string& name) const = 0;\n109:     virtual std::vector<std::string> listTools() const = 0;\n110:     virtual std::vector<std::string> listSkills() const = 0;\n111:     virtual bool addTool(const Tool& tool) = 0;\n112:     virtual bool addSkill(const Skill& skill) = 0;\n113: };\n114: \n115: class ToolRunner {\n116: public:\n117:     virtual ~ToolRunner() = default;\n118:     // Runs a tool with the given parameters. Must enforce timeout from tool.timeoutSecs.\n119:     // Returns the stdout output as a string (or JSON for structured outputs).\n120:     // On timeout, returns a string starting with \"ERROR: timeout\".\n121:     // On command failure, returns a string starting with \"ERROR:\".\n122:     virtual json run(const Tool& tool, const json& params) = 0;\n123: \n124:     // Streaming variant: returns immediately with a StreamHandle.\n125:     // onChunk is called from a background thread with (chunk, direction).\n126:     // Default implementation delegates to CommandRunner::runStreaming.\n127:     virtual a0::StreamHandle runStreaming(const Tool& tool,\n128:                                            const json& params,\n129:                                            a0::StreamCallback onChunk);\n130: };\n131: \n132: class InferenceProvider {\n133: public:\n134:     virtual ~InferenceProvider() = default;\n135:     virtual std::string complete(const std::string& systemPrompt,\n136:                                   const std::string& userPrompt) = 0;\n137:     virtual void setMockUrl(const std::string& url) = 0;\n138: };\n139: \n140: struct ContextFrame {\n141:     std::string role;\n142:     std::string content;\n143: };\n144: \n145: class ContextManager {\n146: public:\n147:     virtual ~ContextManager() = default;\n148:     virtual void push(const ContextFrame& frame) = 0;\n149:     virtual ContextFrame pop() = 0;\n150:     virtual ContextFrame peek() const = 0;\n151:     virtual size_t size() const = 0;\n152:     virtual void clear() = 0;\n153:     virtual std::vector<ContextFrame> snapshot() const = 0;\n154: };\n155: \n156: class DependencyResolver {\n157: public:\n158:     virtual ~DependencyResolver() = default;\n159:     virtual bool checkToolDependencies(const Tool& tool) const = 0;\n160:     virtual bool checkPromptDependencies(const Prompt& prompt) const = 0;\n161:     virtual std::vector<std::string> missingDependencies(const Prompt& prompt) const = 0;\n162: };\n163: \n164: class SkillRunner {\n165: public:\n166:     virtual ~SkillRunner() = default;\n167:     // Expands prompt.prompt by:\n168:     //   1. Replacing {{key}} placeholders with values from params (where key\n... (output truncated at 8192 bytes)","role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_00_lcvzSoNMsbvQLMRp3W9e1366"},{"content":"","role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"function":{"arguments":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/pc/projects/opensassi/a0/.a0/worktrees/a0-session-7aaf7148/technical-specification.md\",\"offset\":168}","name":"read"},"id":"call_00_tczmVLDMwyXUPPyHXArJ4550","type":"function"}]},{"content":"168:     //   1. Replacing {{key}} placeholders with values from params (where key matches a top-level field).\n169:     //   2. Replacing {{tool:name key=\"value\" ...}} placeholders with the result of executing the named tool.\n170:     //   3. Replacing {{tool_call:qualified_name}} placeholders with the short name.\n171:     virtual std::string expandPrompt(const Prompt& prompt, const json& params) = 0;\n172:     // Runs the validator chain. If any validator returns a string starting with \"ERROR:\",\n173:     // the final result is prefixed with \"VALIDATOR_ERROR:\".\n174:     virtual json runValidators(const Prompt& prompt, const json& input) = 0;\n175:     // Executes the prompt: expandPrompt -> InferenceProvider.complete() -> runValidators.\n176:     // Before calling complete, it must verify that all dependencies are present (using DependencyResolver).\n177:     virtual json execute(const Prompt& prompt, const json& params) = 0;\n178: \n179:     // Streaming variant: executes the prompt with streaming tool invocations.\n180:     virtual a0::StreamHandle executeStreaming(const Prompt& prompt,\n181:                                                const json& params,\n182:                                                a0::StreamCallback onChunk) = 0;\n183: \n184:     virtual void setGlobalVar(const std::string& key, const std::string& value) = 0;\n185:     virtual void setGlobalVars(const std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string>& vars) = 0;\n186: };\n187: \n188: class SchemaInferenceEngine {\n189: public:\n190:     virtual ~SchemaInferenceEngine() = default;\n191:     virtual Tool inferTool(const std::string& naturalLanguageDescription) = 0;\n192:     virtual Prompt inferPrompt(const std::string& naturalLanguageDescription) = 0;\n193: };\n194: \n195: class AgentCore {\n196: public:\n197:     virtual ~AgentCore() = default;\n198:     virtual bool init(const std::string& componentsDir) = 0;\n199:     // Processes a user goal. Matches prompts by exact name (case-sensitive) against the goal string.\n200:     // If no exact match, uses SchemaInferenceEngine to infer a new prompt.\n201:     // If inference also fails, enters the forked tool-calling loop (xRunForkedLoop).\n202:     virtual json processGoal(const std::string& goal) = 0;\n203:     // Streaming variant: processes a goal with streaming tool invocations.\n204:     virtual a0::StreamHandle processGoalStreaming(const std::string& goal,\n205:                                                    a0::StreamCallback onChunk) = 0;\n206:     virtual bool resumeSession(const std::string& sessionId) = 0;\n207:     virtual std::string currentSessionId() const = 0;\n208:     virtual void run() = 0;\n209: };\n210: \n211: // === Docker Integration Interfaces ===\n212: // Full implementations reside in ./src/docker/\n213: \n214: class ContainerManager {\n215: public:\n216:     virtual ~ContainerManager() = default;\n217:     virtual std::string acquireContainer(const Tool& tool) = 0;\n218:     virtual std::string execInContainer(const std::string& containerId,\n219:                                         const std::string& command,\n220:                                         const std::string& stdinData = \"\") = 0;\n221:     virtual void pruneIdleContainers() = 0;\n222: };\n223: \n224: class ComposeManager {\n225: public:\n226:     virtual ~ComposeManager() = default;\n227:     virtual std::string startEnvironment(const Prompt& prompt, const std::string& skillDirectory) = 0;\n228:     virtual void stopEnvironment(const Prompt& prompt) = 0;\n229:     virtual void markUsed(const Prompt& prompt) = 0;\n230:     virtual void setCurrentPrompt(const Prompt& prompt) = 0;\n231:     virtual std::string getCurrentNetwork() const = 0;\n232:     virtual void clearCurrentPrompt() = 0;\n233: };\n234: \n235: class DockerToolRunner : public ToolRunner {\n236: public:\n237:     virtual ~DockerToolRunner() = default;\n238:     // Constructor (in implementation) will take ContainerManager* and ComposeManager*.\n239: };\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## 3. System Architecture\n245: \n246: The architecture includes both host and Docker execution paths, with mandatory dependency check and container pooling. The `SystemToolRegistry` has been eliminated — all tool dispatch (both C++ system handlers and command-based subprocess tools) goes through `SkillManager`'s handler registry.\n247: \n248: ```mermaid\n249: graph TB\n250:     User((User))\n251:     DeepSeek[(\"DeepSeek API\")]\n252: \n253:     subgraph \"Agent Process\"\n254:         Core[AgentCore]\n255:         Context[ContextManager]\n256:         SkillMgr[SkillManager]\n257:         SkillMgr_Handlers[m_handlers: xBash, xRead, xGitCommand, ...]\n258:         HostRunner[HostToolRunner]\n259:         DockerRunner[DockerToolRunner]\n260:         SkillRunner[SkillRunner]\n261:         InfEngine[SchemaInferenceEngine]\n262:         DepResolver[DependencyResolver]\n263:         Persistence[PersistenceStore]\n264:         ContainerMgr[ContainerManager]\n265:         ComposeMgr[ComposeManager]\n266:     end\n267: \n268:     subgraph \"Persistence\"\n269:         DB[(.a0/db/sessions.db)]\n270:     end\n271: \n272:     subgraph \"Docker Engine\"\n273:         Containers[(Containers)]\n274:         ComposeStacks[(Compose Stacks)]\n275:     end\n276: \n277:     subgraph \"Filesystem\"\n278:         SkillsDir[(skills/)]\n279:     end\n280: \n281:     User --> Core\n282:     Core --> SkillMgr\n283:     Core --> DepResolver\n284:     Core --> HostRunner\n285:     Core --> DockerRunner\n286:     Core --> SkillRunner\n287:     Core --> InfEngine\n288:     SkillMgr --> SkillMgr_Handlers\n289:     SkillMgr --> HostRunner\n290:     SkillMgr --> DockerRunner\n291:     SkillRunner --> DepResolver\n292:     SkillRunner --> DeepSeek\n293:     SkillRunner --> SkillMgr\n294:     SkillRunner --> HostRunner\n295:     SkillRunner --> DockerRunner\n296:     InfEngine --> DeepSeek\n297:     InfEngine --> SkillMgr\n298:     Core --> Persistence\n299:     Persistence --> DB\n300:     SkillMgr --> SkillsDir\n301: \n302:     DockerRunner --> ContainerMgr\n303:     DockerRunner --> ComposeMgr\n304:     ContainerMgr --> Containers\n305:     ComposeMgr --> ComposeStacks\n306: ```\n307: \n308: **Caption**: `SkillManager` owns both the manifest index (loaded from `skills/`) and the `m_handlers` registry of C++ system tool handlers. It dispatches to `HostToolRunner`/`DockerToolRunner` for command-based tools. All built-in tools (bash, read, edit, git, docker, etc.) are registered as handlers on `SkillManager` at startup.\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## 4. Detailed Data Flow\n313: \n314: The following sequence diagrams show the execution paths for skills and Docker‑based tools.\n315: \n316: ### 4.1 Skill Execution with Dependency Check and Eager Tool Calls\n317: \n318: ```mermaid\n319: sequenceDiagram\n320:     participant User\n321:     participant Core\n322:     participant SkillRunner\n323:     participant DepResolver\n324:     participant ToolRunner\n325:     participant list_files\n326:     participant DeepSeek\n327:     participant extract_json\n328: \n329:     User->>Core: \"find files in /home related to proposals\"\n330:     Core->>SkillRunner: run(skill, {goal:\"find files in /home related to proposals\"})\n331:     SkillRunner->>DepResolver: checkSkillDependencies(skill)\n332:     alt missing dependencies\n333:         DepResolver-->>SkillRunner: [\"missing_tool\"]\n334:         SkillRunner-->>Core: error(\"missing dependencies: missing_tool\")\n335:         Core-->>User: error\n336:     else dependencies satisfied\n337:         DepResolver-->>SkillRunner: ok\n338:         SkillRunner->>SkillRunner: expandPrompt: replace {{goal}} with user goal\n339:         SkillRunner->>SkillRunner: parse {{tool:list_files path=\"/home\"}}\n340:         SkillRunner->>ToolRunner: run(list_files, {path:\"/home\"})\n341:         ToolRunner-->>SkillRunner: [\"f1\",\"f2\",\"f3\"]\n342:         SkillRunner->>SkillRunner: substitute tool result into prompt\n343:         SkillRunner->>DeepSeek: complete(expanded prompt)\n344:         DeepSeek-->>SkillRunner: \"[\\\"f1\\\",\\\"f3\\\"]\"\n345:         loop each validator (extract_json)\n346:             SkillRunner->>ToolRunner: run(validator, currentValue)\n347:             alt validator returns error\n348:                 ToolRunner-->>SkillRunner: \"ERROR: invalid \n... (output truncated at 8192 bytes)","role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_00_tczmVLDMwyXUPPyHXArJ4550"},{"content":"","role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"function":{"arguments":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/pc/projects/opensassi/a0/.a0/worktrees/a0-session-7aaf7148/technical-specification.md\",\"offset\":348}","name":"read"},"id":"call_00_s69ZUYENHmtXL0AY4HZF1667","type":"function"}]},{"content":"348:                 ToolRunner-->>SkillRunner: \"ERROR: invalid JSON\"\n349:                 SkillRunner->>SkillRunner: prefix \"VALIDATOR_ERROR:\"\n350:             else\n351:                 ToolRunner-->>SkillRunner: transformedValue\n352:             end\n353:         end\n354:         SkillRunner-->>Core: [\"f1\"]\n355:         Core-->>User: result\n356:     end\n357: ```\n358: \n359: ### 4.2 Docker Tool Execution (Containerized)\n360: \n361: ```mermaid\n362: sequenceDiagram\n363:     participant SkillRunner\n364:     participant DockerRunner\n365:     participant ContainerMgr\n366:     participant Docker\n367: \n368:     SkillRunner->>DockerRunner: run(tool, params)\n369:     DockerRunner->>ContainerMgr: acquireContainer(tool)\n370:     ContainerMgr->>ContainerMgr: lookup/start container (shared or per‑tool)\n371:     ContainerMgr-->>DockerRunner: containerId\n372:     DockerRunner->>DockerRunner: build command (args mode or stdin)\n373:     DockerRunner->>Docker: docker exec -i <containerId> sh -c '<command>'\n374:     Docker-->>DockerRunner: stdout/stderr\n375:     DockerRunner-->>SkillRunner: result\n376: ```\n377: \n378: **Note**: When a skill declares a `composeFile`, the `SkillRunner` first calls `ComposeManager::startEnvironment` to bring up the compose stack; the tool container is then attached to the resulting network.\n379: \n380: ---\n381: \n382: ## 5. Testing Requirements\n383: \n384: ### 5.1 Unit Tests (Google Test)\n385: \n386: | Class                | Test Case                                                   | Verification                                       |\n387: | -------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |\n388: | `ToolRunner`         | `run` with `split_lines` tool                               | Input \"a\\nb\\nc\" → output `[\"a\",\"b\",\"c\"]`           |\n389: | `ToolRunner`         | `run` with `bash` tool                                      | Input \"echo hello\" → output \"hello\\n\"              |\n390: | `ToolRunner`         | `run` with `args` mode and object params                    | Command receives `--file=test.txt` style arguments |\n391: | `ToolRunner`         | `run` with a command that sleeps 31 seconds                 | Returns `\"ERROR: timeout\"` (enforces timeoutSecs)  |\n392: | `ToolRunner`         | `runStreaming` basic echo                                   | onChunk called with output, handle.isDone() true   |\n393: | `SkillRunner`        | `expandPrompt` with `{{goal}}` placeholder                  | Substitutes value from `params[\"goal\"]`            |\n394: | `SkillRunner`        | `expandPrompt` with eager tool call                         | Eager execution, substitution                      |\n395: | `SkillRunner`        | `expandPrompt` with `{{tool_call:...}}`                     | Short name substitution                            |\n396: | `SkillRunner`