| Use tool        | Invoke `count_lines` with `{path:\"/etc/passwd\"}`                                                                         | Returns number of lines                                    |\n413: | E2E‑04 | Infer new prompt/skill | Send goal: \"create a skill that lists files in a directory and filters those containing 'log' using list_files and grep\" | New prompt appears; dependencies correct |\n414: | E2E‑05 | Use prompt       | Invoke prompt with `{directory:\"/var/log\"}`                                                                               | Returns array of existing files with \"log\" in name         |\n415: \n416: #### Negative E2E Tests (Critical for Guardrails)\n417: \n418: | ID     | Scenario                      | Steps                                                                               | Expected                                                       |\n419: | ------ | ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\n420: | E2E‑N1 | Skill with missing dependency | Create skill that depends on `nonexistent_tool`, then invoke it                     | Error message: `missing dependencies: nonexistent_tool`        |\n421: | E2E‑N2 | Tool that hangs               | Invoke tool that runs `sleep 100`                                                   | Returns `\"ERROR: timeout\"` within 32 seconds                   |\n422: | E2E‑N3 | Skill using `{{goal}}`        | Create skill with prompt `\"Process: {{goal}}\"`, invoke with goal \"test\"             | LLM receives `\"Process: test\"`                                 |\n423: | E2E‑N4 | Tool with `args` mode         | Create tool with `inputMode: \"args\"`, command `wc -l`, params `{\"input\":\"a\\nb\\nc\"}` | Command receives arguments correctly (exact behaviour defined) |\n424: \n425: ### 5.3 Docker‑Specific Tests\n426: \n427: #### Unit Tests (with mock Docker CLI)\n428: \n429: | Class                 | Test Case                          | Verification                                         |\n430: | --------------------- | ---------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n431: | `ContainerManager`    | `acquireContainer` with HIGH trust | Same container ID for two different high‑trust tools |\n432: | `ContainerManager`    | `acquireContainer` with LOW trust  | Different containers for different tool names        |\n433: | `ContainerManager`    | `pruneIdleContainers`              | Container idle > timeout removed                     |\n434: | `DependencyInstaller` | `installDependencies`              | Idempotent installation                              |\n435: | `ComposeManager`      | `startEnvironment`                 | `docker-compose up -d` called only once per skill    |\n436: | `DockerToolRunner`    | `run` with `args` mode             | Command arguments passed correctly inside container  |\n437: | `DockerToolRunner`    | `run` with timeout                 | Timeout enforced (kills container command)           |\n438: | `DockerToolRunner`    | `runStreaming` pooled              | StreamHandle returned, chunks via callback           |\n439: | `DockerToolRunner`    | `runStreaming` ephemeral        \n... (output truncated at 8192 bytes)","role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_00_s69ZUYENHmtXL0AY4HZF1667"},{"content":"","role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"function":{"arguments":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/pc/projects/opensassi/a0/.a0/worktrees/a0-session-7aaf7148/technical-specification.md\",\"offset\":439}","name":"read"},"id":"call_00_2wil39BAxXtgdy22NTYQ3987","type":"function"}]},{"content":"439: | `DockerToolRunner`    | `runStreaming` ephemeral           | StreamHandle returned, `docker run --rm` used        |\n440: \n441: #### End‑to‑End Tests (with real Docker daemon)\n442: \n443: | ID     | Scenario                                     | Expected                             |\n444: | ------ | -------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |\n445: | E2E‑D1 | Basic tool in default image (`ubuntu:22.04`) | Output matches command               |\n446: | E2E‑D2 | `aptDependencies` installed correctly        | Tool can use installed package       |\n447: | E2E‑D3 | Trust level HIGH – container sharing         | Two tools run in same container      |\n448: | E2E‑D4 | Trust level LOW – isolation                  | Each tool gets its own container     |\n449: | E2E‑D5 | Skill with `docker-compose.yml`              | Services start, tool can connect     |\n450: | E2E‑D6 | Container pruning                            | Idle container removed after timeout |\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: ## 6. CLI Entry Point\n455: \n456: ```bash\n457: agent --components-dir <path> [--env-file <path>] [--a0-dir <path>] [--resume <session-id>]\n458:       [--api-key <key>] [--mock-api <url>]\n459:       [--docker-host <url>] [--container-idle-timeout <seconds>]\n460:       [--max-idle-containers <count>] [--default-docker-image <image>] [--no-docker]\n461: ```\n462: \n463: - `--a0-dir` : Root directory for non-committed agent artifacts (default `./.a0`). Created on startup if missing; on first creation, automatically appended to `.gitignore` when CWD is a git repository. All runtime state (b1 socket/pid, SQLite database, skills store, logs) is scoped under this directory.\n464: - `--components-dir` : Root directory for components (default `./components`).\n465: - `--env-file` : Path to `.env` file to load (default `./.env`). Each line is `KEY=VALUE`; `#` comments and blank lines are skipped. **The implementation must overwrite existing environment variables** (i.e., use `setenv(key, val, 1)`).\n466: \n467: - `--api-key` : DeepSeek API key; if not provided, read from environment (see precedence below).\n468: - `--mock-api` : Override the API URL (for testing, e.g., `http://localhost:8080`).\n469: \n470: **Docker‑specific flags**:\n471: \n472: - `--docker-host` : Docker daemon socket URL (default `unix:///var/run/docker.sock`).\n473: - `--container-idle-timeout` : Seconds after which an idle container is pruned (default `300`).\n474: - `--max-idle-containers` : Maximum number of idle containers allowed per pool (default `10`).\n475: - `--default-docker-image` : Default image when tool does not specify `dockerImage` (default `ubuntu:22.04`).\n476: - `--no-docker` : Disable Docker integration; fall back to host runner for all tools.\n477: \n478: **Environment variables** (override defaults):\n479: \n480: - `A0_DIR` — default `.a0/` root (overridden by `--a0-dir`)\n481: - `A0_DOCKER_HOST`\n482: - `A0_CONTAINER_IDLE_TIMEOUT`\n483: - `A0_MAX_IDLE_CONTAINERS`\n484: - `A0_DEFAULT_DOCKER_IMAGE`\n485: \n486: **API key precedence (highest to lowest)**:\n487: \n488: 1. `--api-key` command line argument.\n489: 2. `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` environment variable (from parent process).\n490: 3. `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` set in `--env-file` (default `.env`).\n491: 4. `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` set in `~/.deepseek.env`.\n492: \n493: **Example**:\n494: \n495: ```bash\n496: export DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"\n497: agent --components-dir ./my_components --container-idle-timeout 600 --max-idle-containers 5\n498: ```\n499: \n500: ---\n501: \n502: ## 7. Development Instructions (Revised)\n503: \n504: ### 7.1 Build Setup\n505: \n506: **Requirements**:\n507: \n508: - C++17 compiler (GCC 9+, Clang 12+, or MSVC 2019+)\n509: - CMake 3.15+\n510: - libcurl (for HTTP requests to DeepSeek API)\n511: - jsoncpp or nlohmann/json (JSON parsing)\n512: - (Optional) gcov/lcov for coverage, Google Test for unit tests\n513: - **Docker** (for containerized execution) – optional but required for Docker features\n514: \n515: **CMakeLists.txt** (as in original, plus `ENABLE_TRACE` and `ENABLE_COVERAGE` options). The Docker sub‑module sources reside in `./src/docker/` and are compiled into the main library.\n516: \n517: ### 7.2 Startup Sequence\n518: \n519: On launch, `main.cpp` follows this order:\n520: \n521: 1. **Parse flags (two-pass)** — extract `--env-file` first, then all flags including `--a0-dir`.\n522: 2. **Resolve API key** — `--api-key` → `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` env → `.env` → `~/.deepseek.env`.\n523: 3. **Initialize `.a0/`** — `ensureA0Dir(a0Dir)` creates the directory if missing. On first creation, if the CWD is a git repository, appends `.a0/` to `.gitignore`.\n524: 4. **`--kill-all` cleanup** — reads `.a0/b1.pid` and the c2 PID file, sends SIGTERM/SIGKILL, unlinks sockets, exits.\n525: 5. **Component construction** — skill registry, tool runners, Docker managers, etc.\n526: 6. **b1 auto-launch** — if not `--no-b1` and not in `--run` mode, start/connect to b1 supervisor using paths under `a0Dir`.\n527: 7. **`--run` mode** — execute a skill non-interactively and exit.\n528: 8. **Interactive REPL** — `core.run()` blocks until EOF.\n529: \n530: ### 7.3 Implementation Plan (Test‑Driven, 90% Coverage)\n531: \n532: Follow these steps **in order**:\n533: \n534: #### Step 1: Write individual specification files for each source module\n535: \n536: - For each `.cpp` file, create a `.spec.md` describing input/output contracts, error handling, and edge cases.\n537: \n538: #### Step 1b: Interface assertion tests\n539: \n540: - Before writing any implementation, create compile‑time or runtime assertions that verify each interface’s contract is internally consistent.\n541:   - For `ToolRunner`: write a test that expects `run` to handle `inputMode == \"args\"` and enforce a timeout (even with a stub).\n542:   - For `SkillRunner`: write a test that passes a `params` object with a `{{goal}}` placeholder and asserts that the expanded prompt contains the substituted value.\n543:   - For `SkillManager`: write a test that registers a handler via `registerHandler`, calls `executeTool` with the exact key, and asserts the handler output is returned. Also test wildcard resolution (`system:git:*` with `_subcommand`).\n544:   - These tests initially fail against stubs, forcing the implementer to provide the required behaviour.\n545: \n546: #### Step 2: Write stub implementations with no logic\n547: \n548: - Implement all functions with empty bodies or `return {};` (or throw `std::logic_error(\"stub\")`).\n549: - Ensure the code compiles and links.\n550: \n551: #### Step 3: Implement tests against the stub\n552: \n553: - Use Google Test.\n554: - Write unit tests that **expect failure** (assertions that the stub does not yet satisfy the spec).\n555: - Also write “stub tests” that verify the stub returns default values without crashing.\n556: - All tests should pass against the stub **only** for trivial cases; most functional tests fail.\n557: \n558: #### Step 4: Implement code incrementally\n559: \n560: - For each function, write the minimal implementation to pass its tests.\n561: - Commit after each passing test.\n562: - Use **TDD red‑green‑refactor** cycle.\n563: \n564: #### Step 5: Ensure tests pass – when unsure, consult spec file\n565: \n566: - The spec file is **authoritative**; fix either the test or the implementation accordingly.\n567: \n568: #### Step 6: Use code coverage tool – enforce 90% coverage\n569: \n570: - Configure CMake with `--coverage` (GCC/Clang).\n571: - Run `lcov --capture --directory . --output-file coverage.info`\n572: - Generate HTML report: `genhtml coverage.info --output-directory coverage_html`\n573: - **Requirement**: line coverage ≥90%, function coverage ≥90%, branch coverage ≥90%.\n574: - Any uncovered lines must be justified (e.g., defensive `assert` or unreachable error handling).\n575: \n576: #### Step 7: Session persistence with SQLite\n577: \n578: - Wire `PersistenceStore` (SqliteStore) through AgentCore at startup.\n579: - Record every user message, LLM invocation, tool call, and result to the `message` table.\n580: - Use sub-session tracking (subSessionId + seq) for the forked tool-calling loop.\n581: - Enable `ValidationEngine` to re\n... (output truncated at 8192 bytes)","role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_00_2wil39BAxXtgdy22NTYQ3987"}],"model":"deepseek-chat","tools":[{"function":{"description":"Browse the skill tree by path. Lists available skills with descriptions.","name":"show_skills","parameters":{"properties":{"path":{"default":"/","description":"Skill tree path (e.g. /system/git)","type":"string"}},"required":[],"type":"object"}},"type":"function"},{"function":{"description":"Browse available tools by category. Lists tool names, descriptions, and parameters.","name":"show_skill_tools","parameters":{"properties":{"path":{"default":"/","description":"Tool tree path (e.g. /git/porcelain)","type":"string"}},"required":[],"type":"object"}},"type":"function"},{"function":{"description":"Analyze user intent and recommend skills/tools for a given prompt.","name":"tools_for_prompt","parameters":{"properties":{"prompt":{"description":"The user's prompt to analyze","type":"string"}},"required":["prompt"],"type":"object"}},"type":"function"},{"function":{"description":"Executes a given bash command in a persistent shell session with optional timeout, ensuring proper handling and security measures.\n\nBe aware: OS: linux, Shell: bash\n\nIMPORTANT: This tool is for terminal operations like git, npm, docker, etc. DO NOT use it for file operations (reading, writing, editing, searching, finding files) - use the specialized tools for this instead.\n\nBefore executing the command, please follow these steps:\n\n1. Directory Verification:\n   - If the command will create new directories or files, first use `ls` to verify the parent directory exists and is the correct location\n\n2. Command Execution:\n   - Always quote file paths that contain spaces with double quotes\n   - After ensuring proper quoting, execute the command.\n   - Capture the output.\n\nUsage notes:\n- The command argument is required.\n- You can specify an optional timeout in milliseconds.\n- If the output exceeds 2000 lines or 51200 bytes, it wi